title: Alberta Highway 50
data:
Alberta Provincial Highway No. 50 is a 14.5 km (9.0 mi) east–west highway in central Alberta, Canada. It runs between the hamlets of Tees and Mirror, northeast of Red Deer.[1][2] From west to east:
